LTSP is the Linux Terminal Server Project. It allows you to set up a diskless workstation environment with not much effort. The Edubuntu DVD ships with a feature called Live LTSP that allows you to try out or demonstrate LTSP without making any permanent changes to a system.

<ol>
<li title="action">Start Edubuntu from a Live DVD or USB disk and select the "Try Edubuntu without Installing" option from the boot menu to start up to a full desktop session</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Edubuntu desktop boots up properly</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Open the dash and type "LTSP Live"</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">"LTSP Live" launches and displays a prompt</li>
</ol>
<li title="action">Select an unused network interface</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">A configuring prompt displays showing progress</li>
</ol>

<li title="action">Boot a thin client and configure it to utilize the live LTSP server</li>
<ol>
<li title="expected_result">Thin client boots and obtains a working desktop from server</li>
</ol>
</ol>
<strong>
If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'failed' result and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result</strong>.